The paper proposes a visual-inertial drone system for real-time motion detection, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The system also uses probabilistic models (cs.LG, cs.AI) and deals with dynamic environments, which could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
